column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 KUD standalone products blocked in checkout after IBAN validation
column41:
Currently KUD TV products for Unitymedia as well as for VKD cannot be booked, as failing in checkout with error message after IBAN Validation.

Steps to reproduce for Telesales channel:

1) Enter unitymedia or VKD adress -> new customer
2) Add KUD product e.g. GigaTV Net, 1.{-}6. Monat 0,{-}€
3) move to checkout, fill in customer details > customer adress in Germany
4) reach to IBAN section, type in GERMAN IBAN e.g. DE20700500000003658888 (Any German IBAN can be taken!)
->IBAN validation is running and successfull
5) Select invoice adress as customer adress and do NOT select any different bank account holder
6) Klick on "weiter" and get error message

_{color:#ff0000}Die ausgewählten kabel-unabhängigen Produkte (z.B. GigaTV App und Net) lassen seit dem 01.04.2018 eine Nutzung innerhalb der gesamten EU zu. Aber nach gesetzlichen Vorgaben nur von Kunden mit festem Wohnsitz in Deutschland.){color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Die Prüfung der Bankverbindung hat ergeben, dass eine ausländische Bankverbindung oder ein abweichender Kontoinhaber angegeben wurden.{color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Leider kann aus diesen Gründen die Prüfung auf festen Wohnsitz in Deutschland nur über den nächsten Vodafone-Shop erfolgen. Bringen Sie hierzu Ihren Personalausweis oder eine Meldebescheinigung mit.{color}_

 

We are not using foreign customer adress or foreign IBAN, and also +*not*+ using foreign invoice adress or different bank account holder
It is not the problem, that its going to be validated if there is any data from foreign countries used! The validation itself is correct process - but the result is wrong! It has to be identified by the system, that this customer is allowed to pay the products so we are able to move to the next section.

 

It seems the booking works sometimes, and sometimes not. Or maybe only for specific constellation of KUD products it works. We need to investigate if there is an issue with the software or not

 

*Positive* examples from this morning:
ID: ** 801847; IAV Weboder ID: 6088191
OSF Order ID: 801861; IAV Weborder ID: 6088197

 

Please note: SAME issue is visible on ACC2, although there is still wave 8.1.5 code present!!

Please check possible side effects from CR780 Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandat which was one of the last production fixes and is available on both ACC
column257: Its not possible to order KUD Products in VKD/ unity region

column808:
23/Feb/24 1:03 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
 
Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] ,

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.;;;

Hi Ari,
 

As per the CR780 we are checking below conditions

Technically we have only these additional validation
 * KUD(Cable Independent package with product in category CABLE->giga_app_de) in cart

 * Its valid DE IBAN

 * Its bank account owner = legal contact

 * Its payer address = legal address

If all conditions meet then agent is allowed to continue.

 
*Customer legal contact & legal address* is what we capture or prefill on customer section of checkout

!b117ed88-4bda-47a3-8750-9f38f445a52f.png!

*Bank account owner (payer contact) & Bank account owner address (payer address)* is what we receive as part of *GetPayerAndPaymentInfoResponse* which is {{I1004_GetPayerAndPaymentInfo}} service response we are expected to receive for Cable packages in addition to {{I04_ConvertAndValidateIBAN}} *.*

*!468b5eec-eef3-4ba2-9939-4efeb1a62c8b.png!*

*Here in this scenario one of the condition is getting failed based on the check mentioned on CR780*
 * Its bank account owner = legal contact

 * Its payer address = legal address;;;

When calling cable backend for unknown IBANS it cannot give any data back, and therefore the flow is blocked, as data entered in frontend is not matching to data coming back from cable backend (as its empty).

rollback of CR780 is not possible ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC2 | Getting error message,"Offer no longer valid, Product added or deleted from the cart" while editing offer from offer manager
column41:
While performing below scenario with NBA tip, we are getting error message "Offer is no longer valid, Product added or deleted from the cart" while editing offer from offer manager.
 
*Scenario Name :* Perform Mobile contract prolongation on existing customer with Hardware (set delivery date) via NBA TIP  and send to Backoffice Agent and check status in Offer Manager 
 
*Step to reproduce:*
 
1.Login to Omnius Using Telesales channel with user role as Telesales
2.Load existing Mobile customer having NBA tips added
3.Perform ILS via NBA tip (RETNOBLU)
4.Select hardware and tariff and proceed to checkout
5.Allow all conditions on voice log page
6.Click on sent to BO button
7.Go to offer manager and seach offer
8.Click on three dots and edit offer
9.Observe the error
 
*Actual Result:* Getting error message "Offer is no longer valid, product added or deleted from the cart" while editing offer from offer manager
 
*Expected Result:* Order should edit on offer manager page and order should submit successfully.
 
*Test Data:*
 108175691
107895418
112680820
100251749
111114489
116209002
101485974


Environment: *OPT/ACC2*
PCAT Details : OPMExport_21214_2023_12_22_15_29.zip

column809:
05/Jan/24 5:19 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Realtime archiving via service API (PPM_658127)  functionality was introduced with OC.157796, but due to multiple issues this was not active until 18th Dec ’23 when latest fix was deployed with OC.000158864 in PR env.
 
By looking at the OA1 logs currently real-time archiving seems to be working fine in PR, as also confirmed by Lac in below mail from DB tables.
 
@Ariadne Thun, Vodafone, Could you please brief the issue you facing due to real-time archiving?
 
@DL_VOIS-VF-DE-AT-TEMS_Team@vodafone.com, 
To de-activate this real-time archiving , we have to set below parameter to false in OM core instances and shut down the OA1(goindr) instance.
File : om-core-env.properties
Parameter: om-core.onedms.archive.active=true
Kindly raise CCR to change the configuration, in case if real time archiving needs to be shut down.
 
CCR - Z_SRT02376962A is raised to make the required changes at PR OM.

Please let us know once changes will be done.
;;;

column41:
DSL orders are stuck at state 1280_SEND_CCB in COM after OPM Processing with no error.

*Steps To Reproduce:*

1) Login To Omnius Retail Channel.

2) place Activation Order.

3) Check the Status of the order in COM. It should be 1270.

4) Perform OPM Processing.

5) Once OPM Processing is done check order Status Again in COM.

 

{*}Actual Result{*}: Order stuck at 1280 without any error.

{*}Expected result{*}: Order should Reach to FINAL State in COM.

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.1.5 | FTTH | Omnius sends Access_Supplier and Rollout_Status value in Upper Case to OGW
column41:
Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1

Channel: Retail

Reference story: OS-34913 Omnius_Submit, As a system, I want to pass on the Access_Supplier and Rollout_Status to OGW, so that information can pass to Output Management(OS-34913) - Vodafone Global Jira 

+Actual result:+  In Omnius Logs we can see Omnius sends ACCESS_SUPPLIER value in CAPS instead of Camel Case (Access_Supplier) which is not expected by OM to print  text for HomeID in contract document.

+Expected result:+  ACCESS_SUPPLIER value should be in Camel Case ((Access_Supplier)

+Requirement:+ [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/sites/549498FTTHWholebuyDeutscheGlasfaser/Shared%20Documents/General/06-IDD/OM_IDD_PPM_549498_FTTH_Wholebuy_DG_v1.0.docx?d=w045a663eecd04fb492f0a647b715b925&csf=1&web=1&e=zGfmQC]

*Please note:* for the 1st part of the info text we already had a DTAG bug: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-36175

*For the new requirement there was a change, the second part of the text should be displayed below the 1st part of the text*

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

+*1. DG:*+
 * login to ACC1 - Retail 
 * load a DG address, e. g.: Nooderloog 7, 26474 Spiekeroog
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> DSL & Glasfaser Produkte"
 * select a DG tariff, e. g.: "[R623.5000000520-24] GigaZuhause Basic 1000 Glasfaser”
 * continue with the order until the Order Document
 * click on the button "Drucken"

+*2. DTAG:*+

Sunil Kumar 
added a comment -
 
Hi All,
 
To get the defect issue fixed two things are needed
 # Fix from PCAT where it should send the value as Access_Supplier,Rollout_Status

 # Fix from OSE.

Initially OSE used to convert the Access_Supplier, Rollout_Status to Uppercase and now with OSE fix if Pcat sends the value as Access_Supplier OSE sends the same with out converting to Upper case.

In the current build OSE fix is available and as the pcat is having the value as ACCESS_SUPPLIER ROLLOUT_STATUS then the same is being sent from OSE.

so this should be also fixed from pcat where it should send the value as Accesss_Supplier, Rollout_Status

If the pcat is corrected it will work.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC1/IT | Getting VO number error in POSFE for DSL/FTTH DGW orders with Retail FI agent
column41:
*Description:* 

While performing DSL/FTTH DGW new activation scenarios with retail FI agent, we have observed below error in POSFE.

We have checked submit order request where same dealer code is present as in POSFE.

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1.--Login to POS-FE GUI with valid credentials
{-}Click on Neuer Kundenauftrag{-}{-}> Under Erstelle Kundenauftrag, select new customer Type “Bitstrom Glasfaser” customer from Sprache & Pakete section and click on generate Barcode{-}-> OK.
--Select Kunde --> Firma
--Enter the customer basic details like Firmenname, Vorname, address having homesConnected roll out status, mail-id, phone number, VO-Number, etc. --> Click on OK
--In Anschluss Section Configure below parameters:
-Select Analog.
-Select Telefongesellschaft as QSC
-Enter Vorwahl, Rufnummern and
-Lage Anschluss as Keller
--In Bitstrom section, configure below parameter:
Select Tariff as ‘KA+ (Glas) - Red Business Internet (BP 4.0) 06/23’
-Select bandwidth as 100 Mbit/s
-Set regio-fee (Regio-Zuschlag) for customer.
-Select the Hardware FRITZ!Box 7590 AX
-Set regio-fee (Regio-Zuschlag) for customer.
-In Telefon section, Select Komfortanschluss Plus (Premium)
-Select à ‘Wechsel ohne Rufnummernübernahme’.
-Select Tariff as ‘KA+ (Glas) - Red Business Phone L (BP 4.0) 06/23’ for Voice
-Select all the mandatory fields.
-Select the customer class as “A” for enterprise customer.
-Validations: “Prufung ok” - to check if all the mandatory fields are entered without any error
2. Submit the order from POSFE order should reach to 1270
3. Open the order in OPM we can see at step the order is get stuck because of the error

 

*Environment:* IT/ACC1

*Test Data:*

FTTH DGW retail order id: 764685 Barcode: VDE7601710595

DSL retail order id: 764793 Barcode: VDE7601710793

*Actual Result :* Getting {*}Error{*}: The Order's VO number is invalid in POS-FE

*Expected Result:* There should not be any error.

 

Note : As per discussion with Senthil and Carl-George we have manually added VO in POS-FE now this Issue is Resolved. But we will require fix for This issue

column41:

Address : 26474 Spiekeroog          n/a         Noorderloog      30

Übergabe an SBUS mit Kommunikationsart mail, Brieftyp 1471_AEB_Aktivierung, ext_sys_wo_id 120488717 (kruttika.deshmukh@vodafone.com)stattgefunden.

EKP-Prüfung: DEU.KDVS

*Step to perform:*

Order should not get stuck at step step CLR_EKP_Name

Order get stuck at step step CLR_EKP_Name

Add a mobile tariff like *[KGM1LH30] GigaMobil L mit PremiumSmartphoneSpecial (Sub 30)*

column502: Logic for Gigakombi was changed & there is no GigaKombi available for TV. The markers VB4 + VB5 are not booked anymore. Also for KIP there wsa a change. VA1 was replaced with GKF and GKF is not booked for existing customers. Therefore the defect is not reproducible anymore
column802: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column807:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;

column829:
13/Dec/23 4:42 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):
 * the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
 * the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is _any_ change to the TV package
 * after the bundle is created the TV package _is changed as it now contains VB4_
 * as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

*OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.* ;;;
column830:
14/Dec/23 1:55 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com] [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] 

 
Hari Shankar Malviya 
added a comment -
 
Hi Alexander/Simon,
 
 For extended shopping cart min max equal warning rules, there is not relation with cable post rule results or execution.
The rule which is problematic, is a max(0) rule and service to category rule. So if this rule’s service source expression evaluates to true than it will check if cart have max 0 number of products only from the target category. So if product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not part of the package then problematic rule service source expression will evaluate to true and further it will show warning if from target category we have more then 0 products in cart.;;;

column834:
14/Dec/23 4:54 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], I am not sure if there was any more specific documentation (I will keep searching for a bit), but the following HLD already has a section:
|*Cable artifact rules*
 
The Cable Catalog and PLM colleagues have requested their own rules engine to be applied in the configurator. This is realised with a plugin development where Cable colleagues can upload their Rules Artifact as part of the PLM process. This Rules Artifact consists of the same Sales Rules (in PHP language/cable-speak) that is used currently in ECC front-ends. OMNIUS will share the full-shoppingcart (all packages) to the Rules Artifact, the rules artifact will process ruling, and return the shoppingcart object with modified cable orderlines in Kabel TV, KIP and KUD packages to be displayed in OMNIUS. The Rules Artifact will be called both before a product is selected (on show of configurator, pre-condition) {*}as well as after selecting a product (on adding to the shoppingcart, post-condition){*}. OMNIUS will not be able to have special GUI handling like for internal OMNIUS sales rules when using the Artifact.|

Highlighting added by me.

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/01%20V-HLD%20Vertical%20HLDs/HLD%202.0/V-HLD_01_Workpackage%201_Scenario%201c-v2%2018.docx]

 

From a slightly newer HLD:
|Apart from the Omnius compatibility rules for cable, specific precondition and postcondition rules from cable are also evaluated within the Cable Rules Artifact. *With each change in the configurator (for cable products) the Omnius rules and Cable rules artifact are evaluated in a loop, until a stable state is reached.* |

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_30%20HLD%20Wave%203_Product%20Catalogue-v2.11.docx]

Also present in a newer version: https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_40%20HLD%20Wave%204%20Product%20Catalogue-v2.3.docx

 

 ;;;

05/Jan/24 4:31 PM;frederik.finckh@vodafone.com;Hi all, I have tried to reproduce this bug again, and verified once again that what Simon wrote in this comment is still true. I think it really comes down to the posting rules not being executed after the bundle rules changed the selection.
{quote}Simon Auch, Vodafone (External) added a comment - 13/Dec/23 12:12 PM

As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):

the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is any change to the TV package
after the bundle is created the TV package is changed as it now contains VB4
as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.
{quote};;;

column808:
20/Nov/23 1:49 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Issue was related to Multiplexer configuration - some changes were done on different servers and after that the error message was gone.

Waiting for details from Amdocs, to include in this defect ;;;
column809:
20/Nov/23 2:30 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Just to highlight the issue and fixed done for multiplexer.
in Production we don't have Multiplexer where the 2 services of VORAS: GetOrder, GetOrderList are directly connected to individual environment.
So in PROD: payload validation for these services is set as None/False where due to which OGW allowed to accept the validation of Orderline more than 9 digits where VORAS had validation set to 9  within their application due to which this scenario failed.

For ACC Env : The issue was occurred because the validation of the Payload(9 digit restriction) was set to true. So as of now we have changed the Validation parameter in JESI-- but to have it permanent OGW shall provide these Multiplexer validation as part of Delivery configuration.    ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC1/IT | DSL | Move Offnet telesales order went to 1296(WAIT_SLS) state after 1280(SEND_CCB) state in COM after OPM processing
column41:
While performing below scenario, we have observed that, DSL Move-offnet telesales order went to 1296(WAIT_SLS) state after 1280(SEND_CCB) state in COM after OPM processing

*Error :*

*Result from FIF: FAILURE! 142605::CCM2605 The Product cannot be changed for the first version of the Approved Product Commitment ( ).*
*FAILURE in external action: Result from FIF: FAILURE! 142605::CCM2605 The Product cannot be changed for the first version of the Approved Product Commitment ( ).*

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius with Telesales
 # Perform search for any existing cable customer.
 # Click on "Umzug Kabel zu DSL" button to perform moveoffnet and check DSL Availability.
 # Configure DSL package and click on send contract button.
 # Submit order.
 # Perform OPM
 # Observe error in COM

*Actual Result:*

DSL Move-offnet telesales order went to 1296(WAIT_SLS) state after 1280(SEND_CCB) state in COM after OPM processing.

*Expected Result:*

DSL Move-offnet telesales order should be reach at 1290 state (Final) without any error.

*Test Data:*

Environment : IT/ACC1

Order ID – *761715 / VDE5601706860_B*
column257: DSL Move Offnet telesales flow is blocked due to this issue.

column811:
20/Nov/23 1:34 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi [~satish.dhere1@vodafone.com] 

fix is ready by OGW but there is an issue with the request from Omnius.
according to the user story: OS-33938, the values for Rollout_Status and Access_Supplier should be mapped like so: Data/CommercialList/CommercialDetails/SystemAdditionalData[AttributeCode="Access_Supplier"]/AttributeValue

in the request that you sent i can see that Rollout_Status and Access_Supplier are mapped like so:
DATA/OrderLineList/OrderLine/ComponentList/Component/SystemAdditionalData/AttributeCode



in that case even after the fix from OGW the request to OM will still missed the  Rollout_Status and Access_Supplier values;;;

column1: OSF Wave 8.1 ACC2 - ON HOLD OSIP-1359 Contract Summary: Price of old TV Product is missing (only OSF)
column41:
test environment: test1b /ACC2 Wave 8.1

Scenario: 
Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales 

Rabatt UMDTZBK is added --> this is correct / legacy TV product itself stays with "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service)

Fill in all mandatory information in checkout section and move until Contract Summary creation

Contract Summary OSF:
{color:#de350b}Price "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service" 0 Euro --> not ok, Price should be 20,99 Euro{color}

!image-2023-11-08-15-09-20-446.png|width=364,height=318!

If you see the contract summary for same order placed in other portals like ZHP und MHV the behavior and display on Contract Summary is correct (and they also use outputmanagement, so issue has to be on OSF side) :

!image-2023-11-08-15-10-53-135.png|width=453,height=129!

Test customer was 552907801

order was submitted from ZHP weborder 7836630

column807:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

18/Jan/24 10:19 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am confused as to why this reappeared on my desk?

The very first analysis was by me and as far as I can tell nothing in the comments suggests that the assumptions I had were analysed?

TL;DR:

This behaviour is reproducible with a vast range of PCAT versions (basically any version containing UMDKLM should suffice).

The product has no price configured, but for (unity) inventory products the price from the inventory must be used. 
VkdGateway correctly returns a price in the inventory of the customer.

column257: Unable to to recieved Capture response logs successfully.
column502:
If the SubscriptionID does not exist for a tip in that case this getStackIdentifier function returns the wrong package stack because in this function the stack is identified based on the subscriptionId and in our case, subscriptionId is not available for the cable stack which is why this function was returning default stack value which is mobile stack.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC1 | FTTH DGW fibre products/details with Access_Supplier & Rollout_ Status details not getting properly generated in Submit order Fulfillment logs
column41:
We have observed that submit order fulfillment logs are not properly getting generated for FTTH DG. Details like Access_supplier, Rollout status tags are not getting updated in fulfillment logs.

 

In story it was mentioned that Access_supplier, Rollout status tags should be visible in Fulfillment logs but the tags are not visible in fuldillment logs.


FTTH DGW Address: 
|80639|München|Aiblingerstr.|941|

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login to retail/ telesales
 # perform serviceability with FTTH DG address
 # select ftth tariff and hardware
 # perform checkout
 # Enter Homeid in new connection scetion
 # Generate CS-CD
 # Submit the order
 # Check submit order logs I09 to observe the issue.

*Expected result:* Access_supplier, Rollout_status tags should be visible in fulfillment logs.

*Actual result:* Access_supplier, Rollout_status not visible in fulfillment logs.

 

*Story reference:* https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-34200

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave8.1.5 | EKR (OREVOKE_CANCEL_MAN) product not visible in services section for RevokeCancellation activity.
column41:
We are performing Mobile Change tariff scenario existing Mobile postpaid customer, Which is having future dated cancellation available. In this scenario, We have observed, EKR (OREVOKE_CANCEL_MAN) product not visible in services section for RevokeCancellation activity.

Please refer below screenshot for same.

!image-2023-11-01-17-21-11-867.png|width=336,height=189!

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Winback BO/FO or Retention BO/FO agent.
2. Search existing Mobile customer, Which is having future dated cancellation available.
3. Clicks on Modify package button.
4. Verify EKR (OREVOKE_CANCEL_MAN) product in service section for RevokeCancellation.

Actual: EKR (OREVOKE_CANCEL_MAN) product not visible in services section for RevokeCancellation activity.

Expected: EKR (OREVOKE_CANCEL_MAN) product must be visible in services section for RevokeCancellation activity.
column257: Agent cannot do RevokeFutureCancellation activity on existing customer which is in future cancellation status.

10/Nov/23 12:20 PM;dadasaheb.narbat@vodafone.com;[^RE_ DM Check Point_ Defect OS-46601  __OSF _ Wave  8_1_5 _ ACC 1 _ Correct status is not reflected on order level for Activation  & ILS in Both Telesale and Retail .msg]As per mail communication from Marcin

Hello,

 

After checking the log files, I found that PHP is failing for all statuses on the pvr server:

 

This perfectly explains why we are losing random statuses, sometimes for the package, sometimes for the order. As you can see at the end of the list, the Completed-Success status for the package was also tried to be sent.

 

Please review the configuration of StatusDaemon on pvr server. Apparently, the *PhpScriptPath* parameter in Dynacommerce.StatusQueueService.exe.config points to a wrong file. Probably it should be ‘{*}_/opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC1/omnius/osf-telesales-int-acc1/shell/amqp/consumer.php_{*}’ (after Zend decommissioning).

 

I suggest to compare the whole config file with the corresponding one on the ovr server and adjust all parameters, accordingly. Also, please verify whether all JobDaemon instances refer to the right php files.

 

 

 

Aside Pritam from TID confirm,

Thank you, Marcin,

I have checked and yes there is some issue with config, not sure how status daemon is different on both servers.

I will update status daemon on pvr from ovr.

 

 

Same mail attached. ;;;

column1: OSF | ACC3 | ON HOLD Wave 8.1 | IMPROVEMENT CR to fix DSL Telesales orders are getting stuck at OnHold-PendingDSLShop
column41:
While performing today sanity we observed that DSL telesales orders are stuck at state OnHold-PendingDSLShop. so that orders are not getting submitted to backend. {color:#de350b}*This is only for ACC3*{color}

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

*Expected Result:*

Order confirmation by DSL shop should came from Tivano/Eshop

Order should submit to BE 

 

Test data : 
Order id :  428201  , Barcode : VDE5600000076

Order id : 428193  , Barcode: VDE5600000058
column257: DSL Orders are not getting submitted to backend in case we are changing the sequence on OGW side for OGW order ID
column502: delivery of CR804
column807:
25/Oct/23 12:14 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Defect to be kept ON-HOLD-- currently here the issue is that OGW is creating a BARCODE which can accept max 8 digits where the new sequence id which is changed for OGW order is is having 9 digits due to which when OGW is trying to search customer is CDM it counts the 8 digits starting from RHS where the last digit is ignored 
So in this case the new order id = 900000073 where while searching it is only calculating 73 ignoring all the 0 digits as they are null.
The last 9 digit =9 is been not counted at all as it only does counting until 8 digits which is 00000073 

To adapt these changes --we need to have a CR in OGW to implement the changes;;;

column1: Function AVAILABILITY.hasHighestPriority with parameter(key,value) pairs dosen't meet the fullfillment
column41:
With https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-38712 we expected a function availability.hasHighestPriority(param1...., AdditionalItem(key, value)) which will return true/false, once the given parameters are existing in serviceAbillity file.

The serviceAbillity file will return a list of key-values pairs for AdditionalItemProperty in usual. Please check below example, or attached file oref492_serviceAbillity.xml

<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>*{color:#4C9AFF}ACCESS_SUPPLIER{color}*</cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>*{color:#4C9AFF}DTAG{color}*</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>{color:#4C9AFF}*AREA_CLASSIFICATION<*{color}/cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>*{color:#4C9AFF}00{color}*</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>*{color:#4C9AFF}PROJECT_REFERENCE{color}*</cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>*{color:#4C9AFF}TELEKOM_Großes_Ortsnetz{color}*</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>ROLLOUT_END_DATE</cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>14-JUN-23</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>ROLLOUT_START_DATE</cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>18-AUG-22</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cac:AdditionalItemProperty>
<cbc:Name>ROLLOUT_STATUS</cbc:Name>
<cbc:Value>ready</cbc:Value>
</cac:AdditionalItemProperty>

So with the input above, we are always expecting true for below function call as result:

if availability.hasHighestPriority(1000000, 'GRUEN,GRUEN_GRAU,GELB', 'FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG', 'FIBRE', '(AREA_CLASSIFICATION;00)') == true,  then ....
if availability.hasHighestPriority(1000000, 'GRUEN', 'FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG', 'FIBRE', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;DTAG)') == true, then

Unfortunatelly the function call only returns true if the key is set to ACCESS_SUPPLIER, all other keys would get FALSE instead of.
THIS IS WRONG !
And need to be fixed ASAP.

Attached are 
-  PCAT-refData (whole fixNet Package)
-  Debug Log with function call displayed as detail
-  oref492_serviceAbillity.xml as mentioned above


*{color:#4C9AFF}Below notices after meeting with Shruti, Avasarala:{color}*
just to make sure, that we’re understanding each other correctly.

I’m not explicitly asking for key-value pairs of PROJECT_REFERENCE and AREA_CLASSIFICATION, never !!!
It could be any key-value pairs of the list, of the AdditionalItemProperty list.

As mentioned on the requirement https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-38712 as Important Hint,
“It should look up every configured pair on the same response item …. as the existing function availablity.hasTechnology”, see below highlighted text.
 
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail!

column810: 27/Sep/23 3:35 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am currently trying to reproduce it on a cloud sandbox to gain more insight what actually happens on OSF side, maybe [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] could rerun a testcase on an ACC environment with logging enabled as outlined on [How to get acc logs - Portals - Vodafone DE Confluence|https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/display/PORTALS/How+to+get+acc+logs]?;;;
column811:
27/Sep/23 5:11 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I tested this on one of our cloud sandboxes with v9.17.0-BB123 and cable PCAT V2301_2023_10_00_020 with the mock [Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI.|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI]

Result: during the checkout I can select 1V1 as a TV technician and TECYESKIP as a KIP technician.
The logs indicate that 1V1 is never passed to cable product logic as selected.
I attached the log of the session.
[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322.log]

The log should contain an entry like "1V1|true" which it does not.

I also reproduced the issue with the mock [Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO] which results in VP0 being selectable in the checkout. Again in the log we cannot find VP0 ever being passed to the cable product logic as selected.

[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_VP0.log]

At this point I think this is a OSF bug, since cable logic cannot control when and with which products it is called by OSF.;;;
column813:
29/Sep/23 3:00 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,
as the logs show the PCAT returns VP0 and 1V1 as visible in this case, so maybe we have a different understanding what "visible" in this case means?
My understanding of visible in this case is:
 * the last call of the cable rules plugin by osf returns a list of packages, each containing a list of products.
 * a product is "visible" for a dropdown if the property "visible" in the last return value of the cable rules plugin for this particular product was "true".

 ** this is especially distinct from the "visibility" of tariffs in the configurator which depends on more information like:
 *** is the product selected
 *** is it configured to be shown in the configurator
 *** is the product "visible" according to the last result of the cable rules plugin

*According to the logs 1V1/VP0 is visible in this case but is never selected by OSF even if the agent selects it in the dropdown*

This is even underlined by the fact that 1V1/VP0 are shown in the dropdown {*}which would not be the case if the were not "visible"{*}.;;;

I do not think it is related to CR676 as it has nothing to do with the json schema, but a change in that CR could of course have impacted OSE to behave differently. Best regards

Simon;;;

column836:
06/Dec/23 8:20 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I further analysed this issue and found the following:

Orders created by OSF contain a field 
{code:json}
"apartmentDetails":{"technicianNeeded":
true/false
}
{code}
As far as I can tell from tests the field is always true if and only if the agent selected the technician_yes option in either the TV or the KIP dropdown during the checkout.

This information should also be passed to the cable rules plugin, in the field `IServiceAddress::technicianNeeded`.

After the selection of technician options in the dropdown the cable posting rules are executed again by OSF, but the the `technicianNeeded` field is not set to true (as it should be if the agent previously selected VP0/TECYESKIP in the technician dropdowns).

This can be checked by searching for `technicianNeeded` in the following log: [^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_technicianNeeded.log] 
Notice that the last execution contains `TECYESKIP|true`, since the agent selected the kip technician to be necessary.

For fixing this bug the cable rules artifact logs can be used to check if the technician needed flag is passed to the cable rules plugin correctly.
In the meantime we will try to provide a workaround that might resolve most of the issues as well. We have an experimental workaround since version V2330_2024_01_00_032.
Until this issue is fixed on OSF side and we can remove our workaround again I would keep this ticket open however.;;;

column847:
10/Jan/24 9:28 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

Okay, let me go through your message step by step.

For the first test case:
 * I can reproduce it :)
 * I think that only the TV dropdown is shown is correct (according to the up to now still best documentation we have: [Scenario dimension "Technician appointment" - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=103985437]).
 * I think VP0 being selectable is also correct (again according to above documentation, and to some tests we have [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#216-236]).
 * VP0 disappearing afterwards sounds problematic and without investigating I have no idea why it would.
 ** VP0 not being selected anymore however explains that my workaround doesn't work because it relied on the presence of the technician options instead of the flag.

For the second case:
 * I can reproduce the behaviour :)
 * I don't understand the problem with this though? For this particular example you can proceed either with no technician at all (TECNOKIP, TECNOTV are both selectable) or with a technician (TECYESKIP, 1V1 can be selected together).
 * If the issue is the error message, what would be the expected behaviour if a different technician selection would be made by the agent?
 * If the issue is that the TV dropdown is visible at all: that confuses me a bit as well, since our tests would indicate that only the kip options should be shown in this case: [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#239-259]

column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test address: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München (NE4-VVO)

 

{color:#172b4d}*Please note:*{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}first we thought the Sky Error is related to KIP only, but if we create an order with KIP only on the same address, there is no Sky Error, e. g.: OSF Order ID: 999881{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on NE3 addresses the bug does not appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-58-49-056.png!{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on ACC1 the bug does also appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-39-25-797.png!{color}

 

 

{+}Actual result{+}: KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP is missing on NE4-VVO addresses

 

+Expected result:+ KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP should be displayed

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load an ENV address, e. g.: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[CKH8] Vodafone TV Cable"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[01H:B06] GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

 

– > the field "Anschluss (WE) is bereits sehbereit / aktiv" is missing

column807:
27/Sep/23 2:24 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am not aware of any interface that lets cable control the display of whole dropdown sections. The answer why the whole section is missing can only be given by OSF.

If I had to guess I would assume OSF is hardcoded to check for TECYESKIP, TECNOKIP, UMTECKIP:NOO, UMTECKIP:YES. One of the relevant tests in our test suite is likely:
{code:java}
    Scenario: New cable TV (KAA) and KIP customer without self-install on NE4-VVO address
        Given a KDG service address where "analog and digital" TV is available with object category "NE4-VVO"
        And a KDG service address where internet with data transfer rate "1000" is available
        And self-install is 'not available'
        And a selection
            | productCode |
            | TC2         |
            | 01H:B06     |
        When I get the availability and basket
        Then the products have the states
            | productCode  | state         |
            | TC2          | selected      |
            | 01H:B06      | selected      |

column811:
21/Sep/23 5:30 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;*Guess:* 
Cable product logic tries to rebuild the selection of the agent in each step. This means that certain clickflows are not really supported.

If their are for example two products A and B, A is visible, B is not, selecting A replaces A with B.
If the agent now selects A, A will be added to the selection and the product logic will replace it with B, the agent will see B in the selection.
If the cable product logic is executed again B is not a valid selection because it is not visible.

In this case A would be VP0, and B would be 1V1.

I do not think that there is a simple fix for this issue if my guess is correct.

The two options I see:
 # do not restrict the visibility of VP0 in this case
 ** this would imply that the agent could directly select VP0
 ** since VP0 and 1V1 are mapped to the same dropdown option in OSF -> the agent can only select VP0 together with 1V1, the replacement of 1V1 with VP0 then actually just removes 1V1 since VP0 is already selected.
 # maybe 1V1 should not be selectable in the first place
 ** instead of allowing the agent to select 1V1 which will automatically be replaced with VP0 allow the agent to select VP0 directly instead.

*Open questions:*

Which option is preferred by business?
 * if option 2 is preferred: should this also applied to other portals

What exactly are the affected cases? 
 * likely all test cases where the rule that replaces 1V1 with VP0 applies. 
 * Can business confirm that all cases affected by the rule below should be changed with either option 1 or 2?
 * The rule is: 

{code:java}
Rule 'Replace_1V1_with_VP0_when_ordering_KAI':
When
    selected products contain '1V1' and
    condition 'new_kip_order' applies and
    condition 'digitalSelected' applies
then
    deselect '1V1' and
    select 'VP0' with contract relation set to the main analog product. {code}
 ;;;

For completeness we attach the log of the cable rules plugin so you can check for yourself that 1V1 is never passed to the cable product logic as selected: [^cable_rules_artifact372637.log]

column1: Execution of Defaulted-Obligated rules is not working correctly for mutually-exclusive category
column41:
we are currently struggeling with the following business requirement.

We have a mutually-exclusive category X ( here: access hardware)

 

If any of this Product A of X is chosen than a Product P (here: Product 10004 Shipping_Fee) should be Defaulted.

Only Exception: if Product B of X (here: Eigenhardware) is choosen, than Product P should not be added

 

We build a rule (here: CR006048)

If not B than defaulted-obligated P (Prio 6)
 
First Result:

If we switch from A to B P stay in the cart

 

I added an additional Prio 1 rule: If P is in the cart -> Do not allow P.

 

Result:

If we switch from A to B P is removed, which is fine.

But if I switch back from B to A I get the error

{color:#FF0000}*Die folgenden Produkte: [10004] Versandkosten können nicht hinzugefügt werden weil sie mit der aktuellen Auswahl nicht kombinierbar sind.*{color}

 

+*Expected Result:*+

Product 10004 should be defaulted or removed just by the rule CR006048, no other rule neccessary

 

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

*-ProcessContext ACQ*
 # *Enter any address.*
 #  *Choose any tarif -> A hardware is defaulted*
 # *Switch to hardware Eigenhardware*
 # *Switch back to any other access hardware -> error message is shown*

 

*Details:*

*Defaulted-Obligated - Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>any</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Versandkosten added during ACQ_7994</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProductInCategory</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="categoryID">FN169</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">20099900_sub</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>false</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
            <Params>
                <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
            </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Defaulted-Obligated</Operation>
<Priority>6</Priority>{code}
 
*NOT-ALLOW-Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>all</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Cart contains Versandkosten 10004_8511</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Not Allowed</Operation>
<Priority>1</Priority>{code}

30/Oct/23 9:36 PM;marco.abraham01@vodafone.com;I made some further checks on this topic.

First of all we have found a workaround to make this particular business rule working.

However we still have the issue with a defaulted Product P and the check !cart.contains(P)

 

The example here is:

We have a (initial) default rule. If agent selects tariff A default hardware P. Of course this rule is true also in further runs of compRules

Agent switches manually to other hardware Q of this mutually exclusive category

If we have two distinguish rules:
 # cart.containsProduct(P) -> default product X 
 # !cart.containsProduct(P) -> Not ALLOW X 

We get this kind of error message: X cannot be added 

 

Regardless if the first or the second rule gets a higher prio we always run into trouble that either the product is added (but should not) or we get the above error message.

Please explain how to build the rules to make it working the whole time;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking ES5 on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Self install is selected  in the access details for Unity Orders
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

VKD address: Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum (ABK = no; Selfinstall = yes)

!image-2023-09-06-13-09-31-974.png!

select the Experten-Service Einrichtung for any Broadband Order:

Check the Access details section:

!image-2023-09-06-13-13-05-731.png!

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, self install  is available in the access details

+Expected result:+ when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Technician  should be available in access details

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a new customer on a UM address where ABK = no, and Selfinstall = yes, E.G:Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"

 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: GigaZuhause 100 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Optionen"
 * select  {*}Experten-Service Einrichtung{*}" ({+}with this option a technician is booked{+})
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * fill in the customer data
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > Check which option is selected in Access details

Note:Backend is selecting the technician as expected:

!image-2023-09-06-13-28-30-763.png|width=483,height=125!

OSF:RETAIL:ACC2:Omnius ID:991759

OGW:2695200

CN:1002969303

Unity Backend

20/Sep/23 4:07 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;This can be changed on cable side, but I am relatively sure that this was never implemented for Unity.

Without CR-716 the agent could select both "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" or "Anschluss ist nicht sehbereit" but only "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" would actually do anything (selecting a marker product).

With CR-716 only the option with a valid product selection is left, but functionally everything behaves just like before.
The agent basically just had the illusion of a choice before.

If this behaviour should be changed I think it needs to be clarified if there are other cases for unity in which (at a self install address) the option "Anschluss ist nicht sehbereit" should be selectable. The other ES* products come to mind for example.;;;

{+}Actual result{+}: DSL PCAT rules are not triggered for preselected optons

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a new customer on a FIBER DTAG address, e. g.: "Am Seestern 10, 40547 Düsseldorf"

 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> DSL & Glasfaser Produkte"

column502: RCA: The issue arises because the exclusive product category that was removed is still stored in the array. Since there are multiple exclusive category products and no conditions were in place to check for the previously removed category product, the loop executed for the removed product as well.

12/Sep/23 8:24 PM;richard.springer2@vodafone.com;{color:#de350b}*Please note that this error also exists on the PROD environment !*{color}

We analyzed the debug logs from the ACC environment and concluded, that our developed PCAT rules are executing correctly. Especially because the rules work as expected on our sandboxes, we cannot explain the different behavior with the same software version on ACC and PROD.

That why we assume an environment problem or a software bug.

When we are checking the logs, we can find that CRFN314 is evaluating to true.

 

2023-09-07T12:27:01+00:00 DEBUG (100): q3imnc473pjlb9rp97o501fs6b : Try evaluate service rule. Id: 445, Name: CRFN314: Standard premium Access defaulted if 20090191 or 20090211 in cart or ILS-Premium

2023-09-07T12:27:01+00:00 DEBUG (100): q3imnc473pjlb9rp97o501fs6b : Service allowed rule evaluated to true. Id: 445, Name: CRFN314: Standard premium Access defaulted if 20090191 or 20090211 in cart or ILS-Premium

 

If this rule is evaluating to true, then product must be added to cart.

 

You can find the debug log files, we used, attached to this ticket. We don´t have access to log files from PROD environment.

Please doublecheck.

Regards

Fixnet PCAT team;;;

column817:
29/Sep/23 7:38 PM;shuyan.luo@vodafone.com;*Is this a joke, that you guys assigned this ticket to somebody, who is responsible for reference data configuration :-D*

It is many time said, that with the same version OSE and PCAT, different behavior are given on different test servers.
So the reason could be:
- the (standard-)libs which OSE software included, are not in the same version on different server
- the webserver, or the workframes on which OSE are running do not have the same version or same configuration on different test servers ...

There could be many reasons, which could be investigated by software developers or admins for test servers, BUT NEVER somebody, who are delivering reference datas (product catalogues) :-D

So I would assign the ticket back to developer team, they should write down the instructruction or installation guide for the deployment team, so that the admins for test servers could check, which system configuration maybe wrong due the installation/instruction guide. 
;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

*Please note: there was a change on PCAT side: [[PORPDT-345] BV - Removal of Ready-to-Watch (Sehbereitschaft) Section - DE Jira (vodafone.com)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-345]*

*When booking first KIP then TV, the expected result should be:*
 # *the Access Details for TV should not be displayed*
 # {*}the Access Details for KIP should be displayed but without the technician option{*}{*}{{*}}

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed

+Expected result:+ when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV should be also displayed

 

!image-2023-07-21-08-34-10-642.png|width=757,height=570!

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC2 Retail
 * search for a Cable address, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: "GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV tariff, e. g.: "Vodafone Basic TV Cable inklusive Endgerät (Angebot bei Neubestellung zusammen mit Vodafone TV Connect)"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

– > the access detail for KIP are displayed – > *OK*

– > the access detail for TV are NOT displayed – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2023-07-21-08-39-31-216.png|width=894,height=583!*

*When booking TV only on the same address the access details for TV are displayed*

21/Sep/23 4:32 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;In order to properly fix this I assume that cable and OSF will have to deliver a fix.

According to the answer from [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42115?focusedId=2910953&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2910953 the display of the tv access details depends on the availability of the products TECNOTV and TECYESTV reported by the cable logic.

*Why does the workaround work?*

My *assumption* is that OSF remembers the availability of TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV from a previous execution of the cable logic.

If KIP is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return TECNOTV and TECYESTV as not available. 

If TV is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return either TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV as available.

-> This is something that has to be fixed by OSF

{*}What is the implication of the Workaround?{*}{*}{{*}}

Assuming cable product logic would return TECNOTV or TECYESTV as bookable the issue might persist in OSF, since as long as KIP is selected first TECNOTV and TECYESTV will still not be available from the start.

*Open questions from my perspective:*
 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?
 ** Is this controlled by special tags on products or categories, or are the products hardcoded in OSF?
Maybe [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] can answer this question?
 *  in which scenarios should which technician option be bookable in OSF?

 * 
 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.
 ** Who can go through these test cases with us and determine which of them need to be changed?
 ** Without at least a contact person that can answer this question it will not make sense to start implementation of this ticket.

 ;;;

column837:
13/Jun/24 2:32 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi all,
so, PORPDT-345 will not make this requirement obsolete, it will just slightly shift how it looks.

The new requirements are: if only TV is ordered, show the section. If TV + Internet is ordered, don't show it.

The new problem is this:
If the agent books the packages in the following order
 * TV
 * KIP

then the TV accessibility section is shown, but it should not.

The problem is still the same as described by [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] in the comment from 21/Sep/2023: 
OSF seems only to decide on whether to show the accessibility section for TV when the TV package is opened. So,
 * we first open TV and book a TV Connect ---> OSF sees that 1V1 and TECNOTV are available and correctly assumes that it should show the TV accessibility section
 * we then open the internet section and book some GigaZuhause tariff ---> from now on, 1V1 and TECNOTV are not available anymore, but OSF seems to not update its opinion on the TV accessibility and will display it anyway
 * IF the user just simply opens the TV package again (without changing anything), OSF updates again and will correctly NOT display it

This is something we cannot fix and still need a change from OSF.;;;

column847:
01/Jul/24 7:38 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 
Thank you for the re-test.

The failure in case 2, where the technician option for KIP is wrongly displayed, is again the OSF bug discussed further below:
- when you book KIP first, then OSF calculates the technician option it wants to show for KIP, which is for a pure KIP order on an self-install address currently "Anschluss ist sehbereit".

- when you then book TV, it will not update the technician option it wants to show for KIP, and just show it regardless.

- when you just simply open the KIP package after the TV selection again, OSF _will_ update its opinion and not show the KIP technician section.

We cannot do anything here on our side and would need a fix from TechM side, so that OSF will always update both the TV and KIP technician section, no matter which package is currently opened.

 

About the "Verbindungsdaten speichern" field I don't know much unfortunately --neither how it is controlled nor what the desired logic behind it is.;;;
column849:
02/Jul/24 3:06 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

Contract document's session is processed successfully but pares processing of contract summary  is failed with below error.

We are unable to perform pares processing in ACC3 environment.

In Pares there is no connectivity to ACC3 environment and hence session wont able to process.

2023-07-04 14:56:08,603;ERROR;adeposcr;;90060;[main];(de.vodafone.pares.processing.dao.osfwebservice.OsfWebServiceDao.getOrderStatusForOsfSessions(OsfWebServiceDao.java:143));Error after osf webservice. code:OGWERR-7014 text:Received Order  not found for [SESSION_ID: ORDER_ID: CONTRACT_SUMMARY_ID]:: [2023-07-04_122356_EV486446 : null : 7803392]

 # Place retail order in ACC3 env

column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column41:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

column894:
07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 

The new requirement should contain following information:
 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval 
 * fulfilment started from automatic approval 


 * explanation on
 * what you clicked to create the manual approval order
 * how to approve the manual approval order

Will update here once it is clear how to process with the new change.;;;
